# UI conventions

## Design system

- Spacing: `AppSpacing` (e.g. `AppSpacing.md`, `AppSpacing.gapSm`)
- Sizes: `AppSizes` for icons, button heights, nav rail width
- Colors in widgets: prefer `context.colorScheme` and `Theme.of(context)`
- Typography: `context.textTheme`, not raw `TextStyle` with hardcoded sizes

## Shared components

Use before creating new ones:

- `AppButton`, `AppIconButton`, `AppTextField`, `AppCard`
- `AppChip`, `AppBadge`, `AppDivider`, `AppSectionHeader`
- `AppEmptyState`, `AppErrorState`, `AppLoading`
- `AdaptivePage`, `PageContainer`, `ResponsivePadding`

## Responsive layout

```dart
if (context.isExpanded) {
  return _wideLayout();
}
return _compactLayout();
```

Breakpoints via `AppBreakpoints` / `context.isCompact`, `isMedium`, `isExpanded`.

## Strings and accessibility

- All visible labels → `AppStrings`
- Use `Semantics` or meaningful `tooltip` on icon-only controls when adding new UI

## Example widget structure

```dart
class MyPanel extends StatelessWidget {
  const MyPanel({super.key, required this.title});
  final String title;

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return Padding(
      padding: const EdgeInsets.all(AppSpacing.md),
      child: Column(
        crossAxisAlignment: CrossAxisAlignment.start,
        children: [
          AppSectionHeader(title: title),
          // ...
        ],
      ),
    );
  }
}
```
